&nbsp;
"One thing is certain: we must increase the defence, we must absolutely increase the defence spending and for this reason we need a clear plan in the European Union by the Member States and the common areas of Europe, such as the defence of the European airspace, but we also need more budgetary space for defence," he added.&nbsp;
We must put Ukraine in a strong position, which has the means to protect itself. From economic survival to military resilience." He declared the President of the European Commission, Ursula von der Leyen.

